<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 31 at 6:21PM CDT until May 31 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 700 PM CDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN WHEELER AND SOUTHEASTERN HEMPHILL COUNTIES...
At 620 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Allison, or 20
miles west of Cheyenne, moving north at 25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible. Hail
damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Allison.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.25 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
